.TH SHELL 1 "2025-08-18" GNU "Shell man page"
.SH NAME
.B hsh

Command line interpreter (shell)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hsh
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B hsh
is a simple command line interpreter that executes commands entered by the user. It supports interactive and non-interactive modes and includes a few built-in commands.
.SH BUILT-IN FUNCTIONS
The following built-in functions are supported:
.br

exit : Exits the shell.
.br

env : Prints the current environment variables.
.SH EXIT STATUS
The exit status of the shell is the exit status of the last executed command. If a command is not found, the exit status is 127.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.br

PATH: The search path for executable commands.
.SH BUGS
There are no known bugs at the moment.
.SH EXAMPLE
.B Interactive Mode:
.br
$ ./hsh
.br
$ /bin/ls
.br
hsh main.c shell.c
.br
$ exit
.br
$
.br
.B Non-interactive Mode:
.br
$ echo "/bin/ls" | ./hsh
.br
hsh main.c shell.c
